私下会面</a>后表示，这是一个“误会”。</p><p>无论如何，马斯克和 X 都将从付费订阅者的增加中受益匪浅，这似乎是马斯克再次呼吁人们关注这一问题的动机。由于许多广告商的支出尚未恢复到他接管 Twitter 之前的水平，该公司的广告收入下降了<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/elon-musk-says-twitters-ad-revenue-has-dropped-by-50-percent-202600398.html">50%</a>以上。通过创作者和 Twitter Blue 产生更多订阅者可以帮助该公司减少对广告收入的依赖，尽管该公司需要<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/johnkoetsier/2022/11/14/twitter-would-need-64-million-subscribers-to-replace-existing-revenue-and-cover-existing-losses/?sh=66a0d5eca95f">数千万</a>甚至更多的订阅者来弥补赤字。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/elon-musk-says-hell-ask-tim-cook-to-lower-app-store-fees-for-x-subscriptions-223952210.html ?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/elon-musk-says-hell-ask-tim-cook-to-lower-app-store-fees-for-x-subscriptions-223952210.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 23a755c7-588a-475d-9f65-a425184d1d70</guid><dc:creator>卡丽莎·贝尔</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 02 Aug 2023 22:48:00 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691016481</ingested><modified> 2023-08-02T22:48:04+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Karissa Bell]]></category><media:content height="5013" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/19baada0-3185-11ee-bef7-d3d58cafe7fe" width="7322"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><me